summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 1962 BUICK LE SABRE. THE CONTACT, WHO WAS AN INDEPENDENT MECHANIC, WAS INSTALLING THE BRAKE KIT AND DISCOVERED THAT THE DISC ROTORS IN THE KIT HAD THE INCORRECT CENTER HUB SIZE. THE CENTER HUB SIZE WAS TOO SMALL AND WOULD NOT FIT CORRECTLY ON THE RIM AND COULD BECOME LOOSE. THE  MANUFACTURER WAS ABS POWERBRAKE.COM, MODEL NUMBER: 802. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE ISSUE AND OFFERED NO ASSISTANCE.
